      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GRAPEFRUIT TITO (8) is rarely out of the finish, recording six places from 11 starts. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (30.74) at this track. Expected to feature in the finish again. PAW JERRY (4) had been racing well with a Bottom Up - Restricted Win win three back then placed next time before missing the frame latest at Sale. Expecting sharp improvement this line-up. PAW YURI (7) is a talented type who skirted wide from an outside draw and crossed down to the inside, leading throughout to win (22.82) at Geelong in Maiden over 400m. Fast beginner who should quickly stride to the lead. Was a winner at his only start from this draw. Leading chance again. FLYING DISCRETE (2) deserves plenty of thought at her first run at this circuit.",
